The paper focuses on legal information retrieval and question answering, which are tasks related to natural language processing and machine learning. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.IR (Information Retrieval), followed by cs.CL (Computation and Language), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.LG (Machine Learning), and cs.CV (Computer Vision).
